{"cursor":"4507","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\nA 'curb chain', or 'curb strap', is a piece of horse tack used on any type of\ncurb bit. It is a flat linked chain or strap that runs under the chin groove of\nthe horse, between the bit shank purchase arms. It has a buckle or hook\nattachment and often has a \"fly link\" in the middle to apply a lip strap.\nNormally the horse is bridled with the curb chain undone, then the curb chain\nis done up.\n","linknr":226,"url":"Curb_chain","recorded":1362476867,"links":18,"instances":[],"pdf":[],"categories":["Bit accessories"],"headings":["Uses","Action","Adjustment","Differences in chains","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a4/Text_document_with_red_question_mark.svg/40px-Text_document_with_red_question_mark.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fa/Weaterncurbchain.jpg/220px-Weaterncurbchain.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/CurbChain.jpg/220px-CurbChain.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ee/SweetIronCurb.jpg/200px-SweetIronCurb.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8f/Pelham_bit.jpg/200px-Pelham_bit.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7a/Wiener_Gewerbewappen_Sattler.jpg/130px-Wiener_Gewerbewappen_Sattler.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[],"members":[],"related":["Horse_tack","Curb_bit","Equine_anatomy","Bit_shank","Lip_strap","Bridle","Lever","Lip_strap"]}